'''''Mogul Thrash''''' is the unique album by [[English people|english]] [[progressive rock]] band [[Mogul Thrash]], released in 1971 by [[RCA Records]].  

==Track listing==
Side one
#"Something Sad" - 7:36
#"Elegy" - 9:36
#"Dreams of Glass & Sand" - 5:09
#"Going North, Going West" - 12:01
#"St. Peter" - 3:39
#"What's This I Hear" - 7:13
#"Sleeping in the Kitchen"* - 2:45


*Sleeping in the Kitchen was not on album but released as a single.

==Personnel==
*[[James Litherland]] - [[Guitar]] and Vocal
*[[John Wetton]] - [[bass (instrument)|Bass]], Guitar and Vocal 
*Bill Harrison - [[drumkit|Drums]]
*[[Malcolm Duncan (musician)|Malcolm Duncan]] - [[Tenor Saxophone]] 
*Michael Rosen - [[Trumpet]], [[Mellophone]] and Guitar 
*[[Roger Ball (musician)|Roger Ball]] - [[Alto Saxophone|Alto]], [[Baritone Saxophone|Baritone]] and [[Soprano Saxophone|Saprano]] Saxophones



*[[Brian Auger]] - [[Piano]] Track 4

